And yet it's usually the least thing comes out of our mouth in conversation.

20:20.021 --> 20:28.274
I want to encourage you to do something for me this week when you're out because this week we may see a lot of people out that don't have any hope.

20:29.250 --> 20:37.439
As people are running around trying to prepare for the storm that's coming, what they should be doing is preparing their hearts for the time that's at hand.

20:38.600 --> 20:42.504
I think a lot of times we should be taking every advantage of the opportunity that we have.

20:43.145 --> 20:52.836
When the news is focused about something as catastrophic as a hurricane, we ought to be saying, but if you die without Jesus, what's the point of being prepared with enough water in your basement?

20:54.597 --> 20:58.802
We will tell people to prepare for the storm that's coming when we're not preparing for the death.

20:58.946 --> 20:59.727
that's awaiting us.

21:02.210 --> 21:10.239
And for the people that have no hope, us keeping hope from them is starving them from having a blessed life.

21:10.899 --> 21:17.647
It's keeping them from being in the place where God sent His Son Jesus to die for them so they can have the same hope we do.

21:20.210 --> 21:27.378
There ought to be something inside of us that takes every advantage of every opportunity to give people hope like it's candy.

21:28.770 --> 21:29.491
Don't you want hope?

21:29.511 --> 21:31.653
Don't you want to go to bed tonight feeling free?

21:31.894 --> 21:36.719
Don't you want to go to work tomorrow knowing you don't have to talk bad about your spouse?

21:40.404 --> 21:49.354
Don't you know you can go into any place tomorrow no matter how crazy it seems and you can walk in there and find somebody that needs Jesus.

21:51.637 --> 21:53.038
And I'll tell you something else too.

21:53.940 --> 21:56.082
You can also find people who are looking for Jesus.

22:00.642 --> 22:03.305
Do you know there's a world out there today of people who are looking for hope?

22:05.808 --> 22:14.998
They have gone to doctors and pharmacies and found only things that kind of subside the pain for a while, but it doesn't give them hope.

22:15.959 --> 22:23.147
They have read self-help books until their eyes have gotten bad, and they have to have glasses.

22:25.250 --> 22:29.234
But no self-help book in the world can help them like Jesus cares.

22:30.914 --> 22:38.682
The people out there who are on their last leg, who their families know, we're going to kill themselves if they don't have somebody come and help them.

22:39.022 --> 22:46.710
And Jesus is right there with us inside of us that we're to, you know, to give the message of hope away.

22:46.730 --> 22:49.714
We might be the last hope some people have.

22:53.257 --> 22:54.679
You'll run into those people tomorrow.

22:56.661 --> 22:57.842
People searching for hope.

23:00.194 --> 23:02.977
If you go anywhere, you'll find people who are looking for hope.

23:04.159 --> 23:08.544
And if you're a believer in Jesus Christ, you have hope and you have hope you can give away.

23:10.567 --> 23:12.690
You have hope that you can give them for their past.

23:15.313 --> 23:16.855
You can give them hope for their present.

23:18.577 --> 23:24.144
And you can share with them the blessed hope that one day where he is, we can be also.

23:26.667 --> 23:29.010
If all this is true, why aren't we doing more?

23:31.586 --> 23:36.714
I really did believe that when we get to heaven, it'll be a lot more empty than we think it is.

23:36.834 --> 23:47.431
I heard a sermon one time said, the one thing worst thing going to hell is knowing that you sent somebody there.

23:48.592 --> 23:51.377
Knowing you could have offered hope to somebody and you chose not to.

23:52.839 --> 23:59.890
I've told you before that I have the horrible privilege of knowing that there are people that I

24:00.322 --> 24:03.105
with the school with that died without Christ.

24:03.125 --> 24:03.825
I know they did.

24:05.767 --> 24:08.410
By the testimony of their families, I know they never received Christ.

24:08.810 --> 24:13.335
And I often wonder what I could have done more to share Jesus with them.

24:14.896 --> 24:22.063
And it spurs me on to do everything I can when I come across people who need Jesus, not to hold back.

24:27.488 --> 24:29.170
Not to keep in.

24:29.922 --> 24:34.569
the hope inside of me, Jesus Christ, the hope of glory.

24:36.712 --> 24:48.809
Can I tell you, I hope and I pray that you will become just as convicted as I am of getting the message of hope into the people's hands that need it the most?

24:48.829 --> 24:51.413
Because listen, hope doesn't come from a politician.

24:52.755 --> 24:54.798
Hope doesn't come from a campaign slogan.

24:55.679 --> 24:57.842
Hope comes from Jesus Christ.

24:59.458 --> 25:07.809
And because he is in us, we have hope and we should be giving away hope every single day we live.

25:10.593 --> 25:13.477
We're so glad you joined us today, but you really should visit in person.

25:13.497 --> 25:18.324
So, our times are 10 o'clock Sunday morning, 6 p.m. Sunday night, and 7 p.m. on Wednesday night.

25:19.005 --> 25:23.731
We're located at 582 Rockingham Road, some highway five across from Redway Inn and Bellows Falls.

25:24.492 --> 25:28.658
You can also visit our website at www.faithChristianAG

25:28.930 --> 25:30.510
God bless you.

25:30.774 --> 25:31.442
Have a great day.

